1
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:37,160
<i>So many men chased after me</i>

2
00:02:37,240 --> 00:02:40,480
<i>But I never paid them any mind</i>

3
00:02:41,400 --> 00:02:43,800
You know this song? Who sings it?

4
00:02:43,880 --> 00:02:45,600
I'll use this song as inspiration.

5
00:02:45,680 --> 00:02:46,880
PREVIOUS EPISODE

6
00:02:46,960 --> 00:02:49,520
I'll try to write
something like it for you.

7
00:02:49,600 --> 00:02:52,760
Teacher, I've memorized
all the lyrics you wrote for me.

8
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:56,280
-You can sing?
-Not really.

9
00:02:57,120 --> 00:02:59,800
I just really like the song he wrote,
so I asked to sing it.

10
00:03:04,680 --> 00:03:05,880
Should I set off the bomb?

11
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:10,160
Take it easy.
Wait until Singha walks closer.

12
00:03:14,880 --> 00:03:17,600
Wait, Boss. Not sure
who left these sacks here.

13
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:20,600
It's nothing.

14
00:03:21,720 --> 00:03:23,480
Probably from the wardrobe department.

15
00:03:23,560 --> 00:03:25,960
-Puna!
-Yes?

16
00:03:27,240 --> 00:03:28,600
Why is this here?

17
00:03:30,320 --> 00:03:31,520
Pick up, Dad.

18
00:03:32,120 --> 00:03:34,640
Mr. Sonrak, try calling
the staff's number.

19
00:03:35,680 --> 00:03:36,960
You're right.

20
00:03:46,240 --> 00:03:47,480
DARATHONG STUDIO ONE

21
00:03:47,560 --> 00:03:49,920
Chaiya, he's holding a remote.

22
00:03:50,000 --> 00:03:53,440
Maybe they're waiting to hit the remote.

23
00:04:02,880 --> 00:04:07,040
Ice, please bring these in.
I'll handle this here.

24
00:04:07,120 --> 00:04:08,240
Sure.

25
00:04:08,960 --> 00:04:10,280
Let me help you carry these.

26
00:04:17,360 --> 00:04:18,519
Hey!

27
00:04:18,600 --> 00:04:20,240
-Get it done!
-Okay.

28
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:32,200
Well, these bags of clothes aren't ours.
I don't know who put them here.

29
00:04:33,840 --> 00:04:37,160
Whether it's ours or not, get rid of it.
It's in the way!

30
00:04:39,320 --> 00:04:40,560
Okay.

31
00:04:48,760 --> 00:04:49,640
Whoa.

32
00:04:49,720 --> 00:04:51,080
-What's going on? Hey, Tod, Wong!
-Hey.

33
00:04:51,680 --> 00:04:54,360
-Hey! Keep guard here.
-Back off!

34
00:04:59,640 --> 00:05:00,480
Singha's coming out!

35
00:05:00,560 --> 00:05:02,240
Hey! Watch out!

36
00:05:05,040 --> 00:05:06,320
Don't get close!

37
00:05:07,640 --> 00:05:08,880
-Do it now!
-Got it.

38
00:05:15,360 --> 00:05:16,240
-Watch out!
-What?

39
00:05:44,480 --> 00:05:45,320
Damn it!

40
00:05:46,960 --> 00:05:48,880
-Mr. Singha? Let's go!
-Hurry!

41
00:05:50,400 --> 00:05:51,240
Puna!

42
00:05:56,440 --> 00:05:57,400
Puna!

43
00:05:59,800 --> 00:06:01,840
Chang, give Chaiya a hand.

44
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:02,960
Puna!

45
00:06:04,360 --> 00:06:06,480
Puna, are you okay? Puna!

46
00:06:07,840 --> 00:06:09,960
-Are you alright?
-I'm fine.

47
00:06:10,880 --> 00:06:14,200
Chit, who do you think planted the bomb?

48
00:06:14,280 --> 00:06:15,560
Probably Boss Noo's guys.

49
00:06:16,320 --> 00:06:19,600
Bastards! They were trying to kill me!

50
00:06:19,680 --> 00:06:21,920
Good thing Chart noticed these sacks,

51
00:06:22,600 --> 00:06:24,160
or I'd probably be dead by now.

52
00:06:24,960 --> 00:06:26,720
But Puna got hit the hardest.

53
00:06:28,520 --> 00:06:31,920
Dad, something's wrong with Puna.
She hasn't woken up

54
00:06:33,760 --> 00:06:35,120
I'll call an ambulance.

55
00:06:35,200 --> 00:06:38,000
No need. I'll take her to the hospital.

56
00:06:38,600 --> 00:06:41,640
Let me carry Puna.
Mr. Sonrak, you wait at the car.

57
00:06:43,040 --> 00:06:44,640
I'll follow you.

58
00:06:51,200 --> 00:06:53,800
-Chang, you stay here. No need to follow.
-Okay.

59
00:06:58,040 --> 00:07:00,960
-Are you okay?
-I'm fine. Keep an eye on things here.

60
00:07:06,040 --> 00:07:08,000
-Chart, Chit.
-Yes?

61
00:07:08,080 --> 00:07:11,280
Bring our guys
to guard Sonrak at the hospital.

62
00:07:11,360 --> 00:07:13,480
-Yes, Boss.
-Yes, Boss. Let's go.

63
00:07:31,760 --> 00:07:33,000
Puna!

64
00:07:43,240 --> 00:07:46,640
The family needs to wait outside.
Please wait outside.

65
00:07:55,280 --> 00:07:58,880
EMERGENCY ROOM

66
00:07:59,920 --> 00:08:03,280
Teacher! How is Puna?

67
00:08:03,360 --> 00:08:04,920
We still don't know yet.

68
00:08:06,520 --> 00:08:09,120
-There, here comes Wilai.
-Puna!

69
00:08:10,080 --> 00:08:12,360
-Where's Puna?
-She's in the emergency room.

70
00:08:12,440 --> 00:08:14,840
-And where's the emergency room?
-Calm down.

71
00:08:15,600 --> 00:08:16,880
-Follow me. This way.
-Let's go!

72
00:08:16,960 --> 00:08:18,400
-Hurry up!
-Okay.

73
00:08:19,160 --> 00:08:22,960
EMERGENCY ROOM

74
00:08:26,920 --> 00:08:30,040
Right now, Puna is in the room.
There's nothing to worry about.

75
00:08:30,120 --> 00:08:32,480
Everything that happened,

76
00:08:33,880 --> 00:08:35,600
it's all my fault!

77
00:08:37,440 --> 00:08:40,039
The reason she got hurt like this

78
00:08:40,120 --> 00:08:41,880
is because of me.

79
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:49,480
Ever since the shooting incident
at the singing event that night,

80
00:08:50,840 --> 00:08:52,640
I should've realized

81
00:08:54,120 --> 00:08:55,680
that place wasn't safe.

82
00:08:56,400 --> 00:08:59,200
I shouldn't have let her take such a risk.

83
00:08:59,280 --> 00:09:03,680
From now on, I will end all of this.

84
00:09:05,240 --> 00:09:07,560
I give up.

85
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:12,000
The doctor said Puna is fine.
Small head wound. She'll wake up soon.

86
00:09:15,120 --> 00:09:18,160
Oh no, Singha's son is here.

87
00:09:18,240 --> 00:09:22,440
Go over there! No one's over that way.
Better go that way.

88
00:09:22,520 --> 00:09:25,000
-Please take care of Puna.
-Yeah.

89
00:09:25,080 --> 00:09:26,240
Don't worry.

90
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,800
Good. Have you contacted them
about the special room yet?

91
00:09:30,880 --> 00:09:33,400
I've got the room.
She'll be moved there soon.

92
00:09:41,040 --> 00:09:42,840
Teacher, who are they?

93
00:09:43,760 --> 00:09:45,000
They're Puna's relatives.

94
00:09:47,600 --> 00:09:50,480
-Then, I'll go greet them.
-Wait.

95
00:09:52,080 --> 00:09:55,680
That's too much.
I should be greeting them, not you.

96
00:09:57,080 --> 00:09:58,720
Hey! Don't go!

97
00:09:58,800 --> 00:10:01,880
They're just filling out her history.
They'll leave soon.

98
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:03,720
I see.

99
00:10:03,800 --> 00:10:05,480
Alright. In that case, next time then.

100
00:10:06,360 --> 00:10:09,640
Teacher, has Puna woken up yet?

101
00:10:09,720 --> 00:10:10,760
Not yet.

102
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:25,320
OPERATING ROOM, ICU ROOM

103
00:10:31,560 --> 00:10:33,880
I can see how much you love Puna.

104
00:10:35,600 --> 00:10:39,000
Yes, I love Puna like my own child.

105
00:10:42,560 --> 00:10:43,800
It's a shame

106
00:10:44,440 --> 00:10:47,200
that she isn't actually
Phupha's biological daughter.

107
00:10:49,160 --> 00:10:50,400
If I could,

108
00:10:51,040 --> 00:10:54,680
I'd want her to truly be his blood.

109
00:10:58,160 --> 00:11:00,800
You love her like your own child too,
don't you?

110
00:11:01,600 --> 00:11:02,480
Yes.

111
00:11:04,360 --> 00:11:06,760
Even though she is
Namthip's child from before,

112
00:11:07,920 --> 00:11:10,040
I've raised her since she was little.

113
00:11:12,320 --> 00:11:14,400
I love her like she's my own child.

114
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:18,880
I'm glad…

115
00:11:19,920 --> 00:11:21,440
to hear that.

116
00:11:26,240 --> 00:11:27,760
I'm so touched…

117
00:11:28,560 --> 00:11:32,320
that you love her
and have taken such good care of her.

118
00:11:35,640 --> 00:11:37,000
I have no one left in my life.

119
00:11:39,400 --> 00:11:40,600
Only Puna.

120
00:11:44,080 --> 00:11:45,600
By the way, don't you know

121
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:48,360
who Puna's real father is?

122
00:11:53,440 --> 00:11:56,440
You're such close friends with Namthip.
Don't you know

123
00:11:57,520 --> 00:12:00,840
who she married
before she was with Phupha?

124
00:12:07,960 --> 00:12:12,160
This is your father, my dear.
Your father's name is Phupha

125
00:12:13,040 --> 00:12:15,760
I love your father very much.

126
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:20,440
-On!
-Hey, Thip.

127
00:12:21,640 --> 00:12:22,840
On.

128
00:12:24,800 --> 00:12:26,640
I just visited Phupha.

129
00:12:26,720 --> 00:12:28,440
How is Phupha?

130
00:12:28,520 --> 00:12:32,080
Since you left him,
he's been really heartbroken.

131
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:37,720
He misunderstood. He thought you left
because he had no future.

132
00:12:38,600 --> 00:12:39,800
Now, everyone

133
00:12:40,400 --> 00:12:43,440
thinks you wanted to be a singer
and become famous,

134
00:12:43,520 --> 00:12:45,760
so you left him and ran to Bangkok.

135
00:12:47,600 --> 00:12:50,040
Did he suspect anything
about the baby in my womb?

136
00:12:51,160 --> 00:12:52,480
Not at all.

137
00:12:52,560 --> 00:12:55,640
He didn't even realize
you were pregnant with his child.

138
00:12:55,720 --> 00:12:57,280
Then don't tell him yet.

139
00:12:58,720 --> 00:13:00,960
It's not the right time for him to know.

140
00:13:03,160 --> 00:13:04,800
I want to become famous

141
00:13:05,680 --> 00:13:07,280
and make a lot of money.

142
00:13:08,360 --> 00:13:10,640
So I can use that money
to buy back his land.

143
00:13:11,280 --> 00:13:12,560
On.

144
00:13:13,360 --> 00:13:15,480
I feel so sorry for you.

145
00:13:16,000 --> 00:13:18,040
You're letting everyone misunderstand you,

146
00:13:18,120 --> 00:13:20,280
just to help the one you love.

147
00:13:20,960 --> 00:13:22,480
It's okay, Thip.

148
00:13:23,120 --> 00:13:26,280
I'll do anything for the people I love.

149
00:13:30,240 --> 00:13:31,080
On.

150
00:13:32,840 --> 00:13:35,360
The label is already promoting your song.

151
00:13:35,960 --> 00:13:37,680
If the fans find out you're pregnant

152
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:40,760
without a father, it'll be a big problem.

153
00:13:43,720 --> 00:13:45,920
You have to keep this a secret.

154
00:13:46,600 --> 00:13:49,800
Don't let anyone know this baby is mine.

155
00:13:50,440 --> 00:13:52,720
Otherwise, everything will fall apart.

156
00:13:55,080 --> 00:13:56,240
I'm sorry, my dear.

157
00:13:58,560 --> 00:13:59,720
I really have no choice.

158
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:04,800
You have to help me get through this.

159
00:14:07,280 --> 00:14:08,480
On.

160
00:14:09,960 --> 00:14:11,600
I'll help you too.

161
00:14:13,080 --> 00:14:16,120
When the baby's born, I'll tell everyone

162
00:14:16,200 --> 00:14:17,600
the baby's mine.

163
00:14:19,400 --> 00:14:20,880
I'll love

164
00:14:20,960 --> 00:14:23,880
and raise your child as my own.

165
00:14:25,360 --> 00:14:28,640
Thank you, Thip. I really appreciate it.

166
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:38,960
Did Namthip never tell you
who her first husband was?

167
00:14:41,000 --> 00:14:44,720
No, that's a private matter.

168
00:14:45,560 --> 00:14:47,560
Namthip never told me.

169
00:14:52,360 --> 00:14:54,720
Well, I guess

170
00:14:54,800 --> 00:14:57,600
we'll just have to let Puna
believe that Phupha

171
00:14:58,520 --> 00:14:59,600
is her father.

172
00:15:02,400 --> 00:15:06,000
We'll keep this secret forever.

173
00:15:08,200 --> 00:15:10,600
It might be the best thing for our child.

174
00:15:15,880 --> 00:15:17,400
You're calling Puna your child?

175
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:23,160
I just…

176
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:26,800
I call her that, like how an older person
would call any child.

177
00:15:34,520 --> 00:15:35,480
Hey.

178
00:15:37,160 --> 00:15:39,160
We've moved Puna to a special room.

179
00:15:39,240 --> 00:15:40,160
Okay.

180
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:43,280
That's a relief.

181
00:15:43,880 --> 00:15:46,400
And Sonrak is still there, right?

182
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:49,400
Yes, we'll wait until the room clears
before letting you visit.

183
00:15:58,120 --> 00:15:59,840
Doctor.

184
00:15:59,920 --> 00:16:02,840
You said she is fine,
so why hasn't she woken up yet?

185
00:16:02,920 --> 00:16:05,120
In the emergency room,
the patient regained consciousness.

186
00:16:05,200 --> 00:16:08,240
But I wanted her to rest,
so I gave her a sleeping pill.

187
00:16:08,320 --> 00:16:11,360
I see. Is there any brain damage?

188
00:16:11,440 --> 00:16:15,080
I've checked, and there's no brain damage.

189
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:18,840
It's just a head injury.
You don't need to worry.

190
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:21,440
Alright, thank you very much, Doctor.

191
00:16:21,520 --> 00:16:22,800
-Thank you.
-Alright.

192
00:16:47,000 --> 00:16:49,200
You're fine now. You're safe.

193
00:17:00,520 --> 00:17:04,119
Mr. Sonrak, Mr. Singha called
and said you should take the call.

194
00:17:07,920 --> 00:17:09,440
I had the sound off.

195
00:17:10,319 --> 00:17:11,880
I'll step outside to take it.

196
00:17:16,720 --> 00:17:17,839
I'll be right back.

197
00:17:27,520 --> 00:17:28,640
Come with me outside.

198
00:17:41,800 --> 00:17:42,800
Yes, Dad?

199
00:17:43,680 --> 00:17:46,720
Don't worry, I'm with Chaiya and Chit.

200
00:17:47,440 --> 00:17:49,720
Yes, Dad. I'll finish up
and head back quickly.

201
00:17:51,440 --> 00:17:53,600
You should visit
and get back quickly, Mr. Sonrak.

202
00:17:54,200 --> 00:17:56,520
What's there to be afraid of?
We're at the hospital.

203
00:17:57,120 --> 00:18:00,200
Even here, we can't be too careless.
They might come after us.

204
00:18:03,480 --> 00:18:05,960
So annoying. I get it!

205
00:18:11,680 --> 00:18:14,080
It's all because of my selfishness.

206
00:18:17,720 --> 00:18:20,120
I didn't want it to turn out like this.

207
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:29,360
I want you to sing for me again.

208
00:18:32,920 --> 00:18:34,440
Do you know

209
00:18:35,560 --> 00:18:37,800
how happy I was

210
00:18:39,080 --> 00:18:40,720
to hear your voice?

211
00:18:47,240 --> 00:18:48,440
Puna.

212
00:18:50,880 --> 00:18:52,200
I'm sorry…

213
00:18:54,720 --> 00:18:57,280
for neglecting your safety.

214
00:18:58,560 --> 00:18:59,760
I'm at fault

215
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:02,440
in this matter too.

216
00:19:05,120 --> 00:19:06,120
Mom.

217
00:19:08,920 --> 00:19:10,720
Mom.

218
00:19:12,520 --> 00:19:15,040
Mom's here, Puna.

219
00:19:15,120 --> 00:19:16,880
Mom's here with you.

220
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:22,120
Mom, please stay with me.

221
00:19:22,840 --> 00:19:26,720
Don't leave me. I love you, Mom.

222
00:19:26,800 --> 00:19:28,480
-I love you too, my dear.
-Puna.

223
00:19:28,560 --> 00:19:31,720
I love you more than anything.
I love you, Puna.

224
00:19:35,200 --> 00:19:38,120
Dad.

225
00:19:43,400 --> 00:19:46,080
Dad… Dad's here.

226
00:19:48,440 --> 00:19:50,160
Dad's here, Puna.

227
00:19:53,440 --> 00:19:55,720
I want to be a singer like you, Dad.

228
00:19:57,920 --> 00:20:01,720
But Uncle Tharin doesn't want me to sing.

229
00:20:02,920 --> 00:20:07,280
Puna, if you want to sing,

230
00:20:08,800 --> 00:20:12,800
you can sing. Uncle Tharin
won't stop you anymore.

231
00:20:15,240 --> 00:20:18,280
I… I'll make sure

232
00:20:18,360 --> 00:20:20,120
he helps you pursue your dream

233
00:20:21,280 --> 00:20:22,480
of becoming a singer.

234
00:20:23,720 --> 00:20:26,120
You don't have to worry
about anything anymore.

235
00:20:28,480 --> 00:20:30,640
You don't need to worry about anything.

236
00:20:35,080 --> 00:20:38,800
-Dad, Mom.
-Yes, my dear?

237
00:20:38,880 --> 00:20:41,440
This time, don't leave me.

238
00:20:42,240 --> 00:20:44,240
Stay with me, please.

239
00:20:44,320 --> 00:20:46,960
I love you both.

240
00:20:47,480 --> 00:20:50,520
-I love you, Dad and Mom.
-Oh, Puna, my dear.

241
00:20:51,600 --> 00:20:54,080
I'm not going anywhere.
I'm not leaving anymore.

242
00:20:54,160 --> 00:20:56,880
I won't leave you, my dear.
I'm here with you.

243
00:20:56,960 --> 00:20:58,240
Mom's here too, my dear.

244
00:20:58,960 --> 00:21:00,360
Puna.

245
00:21:03,720 --> 00:21:05,840
Dad, Mom.

246
00:21:52,920 --> 00:21:55,520
Good thing we left when we did.
or we'd have run into them.

247
00:21:56,120 --> 00:21:59,880
You two go home for now.
Don't worry, I'll watch over Puna.

248
00:22:00,560 --> 00:22:04,520
I'm counting on you. If anything happens,
don't hesitate to call me.

249
00:22:04,600 --> 00:22:07,120
Got it. Go ahead.
It won't be safe if you stay.

250
00:22:18,840 --> 00:22:20,760
I'm at the hospital now.

251
00:22:20,840 --> 00:22:22,040
OPERATING ROOM, ICU ROOM

252
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:24,880
Do you see that?

253
00:22:27,120 --> 00:22:28,360
That's Chart.

254
00:22:28,440 --> 00:22:29,760
I think

255
00:22:29,840 --> 00:22:33,080
I've seen someone
who looks just like Phupha again.

256
00:22:33,160 --> 00:22:36,600
-Let's walk around the other way.
-Good idea.

257
00:22:37,240 --> 00:22:41,120
We shouldn't walk together.
Then, you go another way.

258
00:22:42,000 --> 00:22:43,120
I'll follow behind.

259
00:22:43,880 --> 00:22:46,960
-Alright, let's meet at the car.
-Okay.

260
00:22:48,240 --> 00:22:49,560
But…

261
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,360
I think…

262
00:22:53,440 --> 00:22:56,240
That's Phupha's twin brother, Tharin.

263
00:22:56,320 --> 00:22:58,720
He really looks a lot like Phupha.

264
00:22:58,800 --> 00:23:00,880
Why not try crushing him?

265
00:23:01,600 --> 00:23:04,440
If it's really Phupha, seeing you

266
00:23:05,760 --> 00:23:07,240
will make him want to get revenge.

267
00:23:08,280 --> 00:23:10,320
Alright, I'll give it a try.

268
00:23:19,120 --> 00:23:22,360
Phupha, do you remember me?

269
00:23:25,040 --> 00:23:25,960
I don't remember.

270
00:23:26,560 --> 00:23:29,160
Then tell me, who are you?

271
00:23:30,880 --> 00:23:32,200
Tell me, now!

272
00:23:34,760 --> 00:23:37,840
You're Phupha, aren't you?

273
00:23:48,360 --> 00:23:51,800
I never imagined Phupha
would pass away so young.

274
00:23:52,440 --> 00:23:55,800
His song was just becoming popular,
and he sang so well.

275
00:23:56,440 --> 00:23:57,920
Such a pity.

276
00:23:58,560 --> 00:23:59,760
What a shame.

277
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:01,960
Tharin, who are you

278
00:24:02,040 --> 00:24:03,880
going to stay with now,
losing both your brother

279
00:24:03,960 --> 00:24:06,480
and sister-in-law like this?

280
00:24:06,560 --> 00:24:09,560
I'll stay with Puna, my niece.

281
00:24:10,080 --> 00:24:12,880
I can't believe Phupha had a twin

282
00:24:12,960 --> 00:24:15,120
who looks exactly like him.

283
00:24:15,760 --> 00:24:17,720
If he didn't have that limp,

284
00:24:18,320 --> 00:24:20,200
I'd think they were the same person.

285
00:24:26,880 --> 00:24:28,960
But what if they swapped places?

286
00:24:35,720 --> 00:24:37,520
If that's the case,
we still can't be too sure.

287
00:24:42,240 --> 00:24:43,840
Go take care of it.

288
00:24:44,920 --> 00:24:45,880
Yes, sir.

289
00:24:51,560 --> 00:24:53,760
You're Phupha, aren't you?

290
00:24:56,040 --> 00:24:57,240
Don't!

291
00:24:58,400 --> 00:25:00,560
Tell me! Are you…

292
00:25:00,640 --> 00:25:02,080
Are you Phupha?

293
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,640
No!

294
00:25:05,720 --> 00:25:07,200
He's not Phupha!

295
00:25:07,280 --> 00:25:09,960
His name is Tharin. Don't hurt him.

296
00:25:10,040 --> 00:25:13,520
Phupha could fight. This is Tharin.

297
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:15,560
He is sick. He can't fight.

298
00:25:16,320 --> 00:25:17,440
Please, don't hurt him.

299
00:25:17,520 --> 00:25:20,200
Oh no! Don't!

300
00:25:20,280 --> 00:25:22,040
Don't hurt him!

301
00:25:22,120 --> 00:25:23,040
-Don't!
-Hey!

302
00:25:23,120 --> 00:25:24,720
What are you doing?

303
00:25:25,640 --> 00:25:26,840
Hey, let's go!

304
00:25:28,560 --> 00:25:31,640
Tharin, are you okay?

305
00:25:33,160 --> 00:25:34,080
Tharin.

306
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:36,280
I'm fine.

307
00:25:37,320 --> 00:25:38,840
-Sroi, are you okay?
-Yeah.

308
00:25:43,040 --> 00:25:47,120
Well? I'm asking who the hell you are!

309
00:25:49,720 --> 00:25:54,360
I'm Tharin, Phupha's brother.

310
00:25:55,640 --> 00:25:57,280
Tharin, huh?

311
00:25:58,240 --> 00:26:02,360
You think you can fool me
like that, Phupha?

312
00:26:02,440 --> 00:26:03,480
Take this!

313
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:05,000
-Get him!
-Yes.

314
00:26:14,360 --> 00:26:15,560
Yes, Mr.Kitti.

315
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:18,040
You've beaten him, right?

316
00:26:18,720 --> 00:26:20,520
-Yes.
-Did he fight back?

317
00:26:20,600 --> 00:26:21,760
Not at all.

318
00:26:22,680 --> 00:26:25,320
He just lay there and took it like a dog.

319
00:26:25,400 --> 00:26:27,800
So that means he's not Phupha.

320
00:26:29,080 --> 00:26:32,840
Phupha wouldn't go down so easily.
He wouldn't just take the kicks.

321
00:26:34,880 --> 00:26:37,480
If it's Tharin, his twin brother,

322
00:26:38,360 --> 00:26:42,320
he's weak, a coward.

323
00:26:44,320 --> 00:26:48,720
You could kick him to death,
and he still wouldn't fight. Let him go.

324
00:26:48,800 --> 00:26:49,680
Understood, Boss.

325
00:26:55,640 --> 00:26:56,640
Hey, that's enough.

326
00:27:01,720 --> 00:27:03,000
-Let's go.
-Go.

327
00:27:15,600 --> 00:27:17,200
Are you okay?

328
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:20,040
Why did you let them beat you like that?

329
00:27:23,440 --> 00:27:24,480
I'm fine.

330
00:27:27,000 --> 00:27:29,480
I did it to keep everyone safe.

331
00:27:43,520 --> 00:27:44,440
Thanks, man.

332
00:27:45,880 --> 00:27:47,640
Boss, I have a plan

333
00:27:48,280 --> 00:27:49,520
to assassinate Singha.

334
00:27:50,680 --> 00:27:52,520
Good job, Pleaw!

335
00:27:53,960 --> 00:27:56,080
Good!

336
00:28:02,680 --> 00:28:06,360
DARATHONG MUSIC

337
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:08,080
The other day,

338
00:28:08,160 --> 00:28:11,280
Tod told me he saw Boss Noo and Pleaw

339
00:28:11,880 --> 00:28:13,800
at Dong Maprao market,

340
00:28:14,440 --> 00:28:16,000
eating fish maw soup.

341
00:28:16,920 --> 00:28:20,240
-So what?
-Got word from the locals.

342
00:28:20,320 --> 00:28:23,880
They've been going there almost every day.

343
00:28:26,320 --> 00:28:27,760
If you want to get back at them,

344
00:28:28,360 --> 00:28:31,120
I think we have a chance now, sir.

345
00:28:35,200 --> 00:28:38,880
Go get the men ready, then crush them.

346
00:28:39,480 --> 00:28:40,400
Yes, sir.

347
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:41,840
Wait.

348
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:45,200
Don't forget to blow his head off.

349
00:28:45,280 --> 00:28:46,920
Don't let him get away.

350
00:28:48,520 --> 00:28:52,600
Got it. I'll take charge
of this one myself.

351
00:29:00,440 --> 00:29:01,480
What's going on?

352
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:11,200
DARATHONG MUSIC

353
00:29:18,280 --> 00:29:20,560
They're planning to take down
Boss Noo at the market.

354
00:29:20,640 --> 00:29:22,560
These guys are so bold.

355
00:29:23,920 --> 00:29:26,760
Can you find a way
to send word to Captain Tom?

356
00:29:26,840 --> 00:29:29,040
See if he can patrol around the market.

357
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:32,960
I'll try. I might need
Uncle Sergeant's informants to help.

358
00:29:33,040 --> 00:29:36,200
Some of them also send info
to Corporal Chom,

359
00:29:36,280 --> 00:29:37,520
Uncle Sergeant's friend.

360
00:29:38,120 --> 00:29:41,280
Let me tell you. Kitti is going to be
in charge of this one.

361
00:29:43,440 --> 00:29:44,400
What's your plan?

362
00:29:45,320 --> 00:29:46,440
You'll find out soon.

363
00:30:10,880 --> 00:30:11,840
Hey, Khod.

364
00:30:11,920 --> 00:30:15,520
Make sure to get everything.
I'm heading to the fish maw soup shop.

365
00:30:15,600 --> 00:30:16,520
Got it, Boss.

366
00:30:17,040 --> 00:30:19,120
-It's still open, right?
-Yes, Boss.

367
00:30:19,880 --> 00:30:20,840
Let's go.

368
00:30:25,200 --> 00:30:26,160
Wait.

369
00:30:26,240 --> 00:30:27,680
Gunshots, Captain.

370
00:30:32,400 --> 00:30:34,720
-Just like the informant reported.
-Hurry up!

371
00:30:51,800 --> 00:30:54,040
Take them down! Don't let them get away!

372
00:30:55,440 --> 00:30:58,720
There are too many. We can't handle them.
We should retreat, Boss.

373
00:30:59,440 --> 00:31:00,440
This is the police!

374
00:31:02,280 --> 00:31:03,560
Drop your weapons!

375
00:31:10,920 --> 00:31:12,360
Run! Let's go!

376
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,920
Follow them!

377
00:31:16,360 --> 00:31:18,920
Let Boss Noo go for now. Let's go!

378
00:31:19,520 --> 00:31:20,480
Let's go!

379
00:31:25,600 --> 00:31:26,440
Hey!

380
00:31:27,040 --> 00:31:28,520
-Come here!
-Hey, Khod!

381
00:31:29,240 --> 00:31:32,160
-Pleaw, get him out of here!
-Let's go, Boss!

382
00:31:34,040 --> 00:31:35,800
-Hey!
-Help me!

383
00:31:35,880 --> 00:31:38,560
Stay back! If you come
any closer, she dies!

384
00:31:38,640 --> 00:31:39,640
Stop!

385
00:31:40,360 --> 00:31:43,040
Don't harm the hostage and surrender now!

386
00:31:43,120 --> 00:31:44,280
Step back!

387
00:31:51,920 --> 00:31:54,520
Sorry, do you recognize this criminal?

388
00:31:54,600 --> 00:31:57,320
No, I don't. I don't think
he's from around here.

389
00:32:03,720 --> 00:32:05,200
I told you to move back!

390
00:32:06,480 --> 00:32:07,320
Stay back!

391
00:32:30,120 --> 00:32:31,160
Take him into custody.

392
00:32:33,240 --> 00:32:34,360
-Get up.
-Come on.

393
00:32:35,800 --> 00:32:36,880
Bring him to the station.

394
00:32:41,080 --> 00:32:42,840
Alright, let's go.

395
00:32:42,920 --> 00:32:44,720
Wait, don't go yet.

396
00:32:45,960 --> 00:32:47,680
-What's up, Captain?
-We'll talk at the station.

397
00:32:48,760 --> 00:32:49,920
-What's going on?
-Let's go.

398
00:32:50,520 --> 00:32:52,320
Are we being arrested?

399
00:32:53,720 --> 00:32:54,640
You'll find out soon.

400
00:32:58,440 --> 00:32:59,480
Who are you guys, really?

401
00:33:00,560 --> 00:33:02,920
I'm a YouTuber.

402
00:33:03,000 --> 00:33:04,840
My name is Chaiya.

403
00:33:04,920 --> 00:33:07,080
And I'm Manat, Uncle Sergeant's nephew.

404
00:33:07,600 --> 00:33:10,400
The way you fought
with the criminal earlier…

405
00:33:10,480 --> 00:33:13,960
-Cool, right?
-What's cooler than cool?

406
00:33:14,480 --> 00:33:18,120
-Legit.
-A thug look but legit. Unbelievable!

407
00:33:18,200 --> 00:33:19,920
Both handsome and skilled.

408
00:33:24,360 --> 00:33:26,800
Looking at you,
it doesn't seem like you guys

409
00:33:26,880 --> 00:33:29,240
are thugs, but it looks like…

410
00:33:31,400 --> 00:33:32,680
Captain.

411
00:33:34,200 --> 00:33:36,920
-The superintendent wants to see you.
-I'm busy with an investigation.

412
00:33:37,560 --> 00:33:39,880
But he ordered me to bring you now.

413
00:33:42,240 --> 00:33:44,760
Don't go anywhere yet.
We're not done talking.

414
00:33:48,800 --> 00:33:49,640
Let's go.

415
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:56,080
It looks like he might
be suspicious of us.

416
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:00,120
From the way we fought earlier,

417
00:34:00,640 --> 00:34:02,000
it looked like police tactics.

418
00:34:14,639 --> 00:34:17,840
With a shooting like this,
we can't just let them go so easily.

419
00:34:17,920 --> 00:34:19,800
At least, we need to interrogate them.

420
00:34:19,880 --> 00:34:21,520
What else do you need to ask them?

421
00:34:22,159 --> 00:34:24,840
It's clearly because of Boss Noo's people.

422
00:34:25,360 --> 00:34:27,280
We should be going after them.

423
00:34:30,800 --> 00:34:32,679
I apologize, Captain.

424
00:34:33,320 --> 00:34:35,719
But the people you've detained

425
00:34:35,800 --> 00:34:38,520
are employees of Darathong Music,

426
00:34:38,600 --> 00:34:39,760
not criminals.

427
00:34:40,920 --> 00:34:42,840
I'll have to take them back with me.

428
00:34:42,920 --> 00:34:45,400
No, I'm not done questioning them yet.

429
00:34:45,480 --> 00:34:46,960
If you're not done, just stop.

430
00:34:48,480 --> 00:34:51,280
Why do you keep questioning
so much? Let them go.

431
00:34:52,920 --> 00:34:55,199
You're really hardworking, Captain.

432
00:34:55,960 --> 00:34:58,200
I guess you'll be getting a promotion

433
00:34:59,280 --> 00:35:00,680
to the border next year.

434
00:35:03,600 --> 00:35:04,960
Superintendent.

435
00:35:05,040 --> 00:35:07,800
Everything's good here, right?
Then, I'll take my leave.

436
00:35:08,520 --> 00:35:10,840
I'll come by to check out the amulets
at your place.

437
00:35:10,920 --> 00:35:11,960
Hm.

438
00:35:12,040 --> 00:35:15,520
Sure, sir. Whenever you're free,
just stop by.

439
00:35:26,920 --> 00:35:30,280
Sir, thank you so much
for helping get us out of the station.

440
00:35:30,360 --> 00:35:33,800
If it weren't for you,
we'd be spending the night in jail.

441
00:35:34,960 --> 00:35:39,400
What got into you two
to help the villagers like that?

442
00:35:39,480 --> 00:35:43,160
I saw the villagers were clueless,
so I went in to help.

443
00:35:43,880 --> 00:35:47,280
You think you're so great, huh?
I'll find something for you to do.

444
00:35:53,520 --> 00:35:55,520
What kind of work
do you think he'll have us do?

445
00:35:56,880 --> 00:36:00,560
If it's their kind of work,
It's probably about drugs.

446
00:36:01,960 --> 00:36:03,320
That plays right into our hands.

447
00:36:10,000 --> 00:36:13,320
DARATHONG MUSIC

448
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:17,560
Singha.

449
00:36:18,560 --> 00:36:21,720
What do you think about Chaiya and Manat

450
00:36:21,800 --> 00:36:23,760
helping the hostage?

451
00:36:25,120 --> 00:36:27,600
I've suspected they might be cops.

452
00:36:28,760 --> 00:36:33,320
So, I had Chit check
with my allies in the central police.

453
00:36:34,320 --> 00:36:38,200
They said there's no record
of them ever being cops.

454
00:36:41,160 --> 00:36:44,160
If they have no record, then it's fine.

455
00:36:45,080 --> 00:36:46,480
These guys are daring.

456
00:36:47,760 --> 00:36:50,600
But for me, that's skill.

457
00:36:50,680 --> 00:36:52,480
You already know that.

458
00:36:52,560 --> 00:36:55,120
They've saved Sonrak many times.

459
00:36:56,560 --> 00:36:57,720
I think

460
00:36:58,560 --> 00:37:01,200
we've got some real talent
on our hands, Singha.

461
00:37:03,640 --> 00:37:06,680
So, you want Chaiya and Manat
to work with you, right?

462
00:37:08,080 --> 00:37:09,040
Yeah.

463
00:37:09,680 --> 00:37:13,320
Their skills are good.
If they end up with someone else,

464
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:15,880
it'll be bad for us.

465
00:37:15,960 --> 00:37:18,520
Since they're with us now,

466
00:37:19,120 --> 00:37:20,880
we should make use of them.

467
00:37:20,960 --> 00:37:23,080
Fine, I don't mind.

468
00:37:23,840 --> 00:37:26,760
As long as we can eliminate
Boss Noo quickly.

469
00:37:28,120 --> 00:37:31,840
He's getting out of hand.

470
00:37:34,080 --> 00:37:38,000
Wait a little longer, my friend.
I'm ordering a big shipment of weapons.

471
00:37:39,000 --> 00:37:41,200
Once those new weapons arrive,

472
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:44,560
we'll take him down.

473
00:37:57,800 --> 00:38:01,160
-How's the dizziness now?
-I'm fine now.

474
00:38:01,240 --> 00:38:04,000
Alright. How's your vision?
Any blurred vision?

475
00:38:04,080 --> 00:38:06,520
No blurred vision, and my sight is normal.

476
00:38:06,600 --> 00:38:10,960
Alright, you can go home today.
Just wait while I arrange the discharge.

477
00:38:11,840 --> 00:38:13,960
-Thank you so much, Doctor.
-You're welcome.

478
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:27,280
Puna, what did the doctor say?

479
00:38:27,360 --> 00:38:29,320
He said I can go home now.

480
00:38:32,320 --> 00:38:34,920
Puna, don't worry about the expenses.

481
00:38:35,000 --> 00:38:37,360
I'll have the company
take care of everything for you.

482
00:38:40,600 --> 00:38:43,920
Thank you so much, Mr. Sonrak,
for always taking care of me.

483
00:38:45,160 --> 00:38:46,560
It's no trouble.

484
00:38:48,240 --> 00:38:49,440
Thank you too, Chaiya.

485
00:38:55,800 --> 00:38:58,680
If it weren't for you,
I'd probably be dead by now.

486
00:39:02,240 --> 00:39:04,520
-You're okay, right?
-Chaiya is fine.

487
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,440
If he was going to die,
he'd be dead by now.

488
00:39:09,520 --> 00:39:10,440
Right?

489
00:39:13,080 --> 00:39:15,960
Yeah, people like me are hard to kill.

490
00:39:16,040 --> 00:39:17,640
Don't worry about me.

491
00:39:18,840 --> 00:39:20,480
Take care of yourself.

492
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:28,520
I need to speak to Puna alone.
You can go for now.

493
00:39:34,960 --> 00:39:35,880
You too, Teacher.

494
00:39:39,400 --> 00:39:40,240
Alright.

495
00:39:48,400 --> 00:39:51,000
Puna, do you know
how much I worry about you?

496
00:39:56,520 --> 00:39:58,120
Thank you so much.

497
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:01,840
Puna, before you leave,
please wait for me.

498
00:40:01,920 --> 00:40:04,640
If I get back in time,
I'll take you home, okay?

499
00:40:04,720 --> 00:40:08,320
It's okay. I've already made plans
with Teacher Mueangphrai.

500
00:40:08,840 --> 00:40:11,320
Don't you have any work
scheduled today, Mr. Sonrak?

501
00:40:12,160 --> 00:40:13,640
I have to go to Bangkok.

502
00:40:14,600 --> 00:40:16,000
I'll be back quickly.

503
00:40:17,080 --> 00:40:18,960
Hurry up, or you'll be late.

504
00:40:21,960 --> 00:40:24,000
Alright, then. I'm going.

505
00:40:25,040 --> 00:40:26,880
-I really care about you, Puna.
-Thank you.

506
00:40:46,160 --> 00:40:48,720
-Puna.
-Puna.

507
00:40:49,680 --> 00:40:52,560
Uncle, what happened?

508
00:40:54,200 --> 00:40:57,160
Just a little accident. It's nothing.

509
00:40:57,240 --> 00:40:58,800
Really? But why…

510
00:40:58,880 --> 00:41:01,520
I'm a man. Something like this is nothing.

511
00:41:05,880 --> 00:41:06,920
Puna.

512
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:11,480
I'm so sorry for hurting you

513
00:41:11,560 --> 00:41:13,080
because of my selfishness.

514
00:41:14,400 --> 00:41:17,080
I truly feel guilty.

515
00:41:19,440 --> 00:41:23,360
From now on, you won't have to go
to Darathong Music anymore.

516
00:41:25,840 --> 00:41:28,120
I won't let you risk your life
like that again.

517
00:41:29,760 --> 00:41:34,320
But I still haven't completed my job.
I need to get that teddy bear out.

518
00:41:34,920 --> 00:41:38,240
Forget about it.
Don't get involved with them anymore.

519
00:41:39,480 --> 00:41:41,480
I've endured for 20 years.

520
00:41:42,840 --> 00:41:46,560
For the rest of my life,
I'll continue to endure.

521
00:41:51,280 --> 00:41:54,800
We won't let you risk your life
like that again.

522
00:41:55,840 --> 00:41:58,320
In the future, if you want to be a singer,

523
00:41:58,400 --> 00:42:02,400
I'll find another way
to help you pursue your dream.

524
00:42:08,520 --> 00:42:12,160
But if in the future I become a singer

525
00:42:14,320 --> 00:42:17,920
and someone says
I'm the child of Phupha Thararin,

526
00:42:20,000 --> 00:42:22,280
the singer who died because of a scandal…

527
00:42:28,040 --> 00:42:29,880
how would you want me to feel?

528
00:42:33,760 --> 00:42:35,040
Puna.

529
00:42:40,960 --> 00:42:44,360
I can't just sit back

530
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:50,160
while my parents are slandered unfairly

531
00:42:50,800 --> 00:42:52,840
without doing anything.

532
00:43:11,000 --> 00:43:14,960
Uncle and Aunt Wilai,
don't worry about my safety.

533
00:43:16,080 --> 00:43:17,920
No matter how hard it gets,

534
00:43:18,680 --> 00:43:20,400
I'll endure it,

535
00:43:21,360 --> 00:43:23,200
so that my parents

536
00:43:24,000 --> 00:43:25,480
will get the justice they deserve.

537
00:43:39,120 --> 00:43:42,520
I never expected Puna
to be this determined.

538
00:43:44,320 --> 00:43:45,760
I'm not surprised.

539
00:43:46,360 --> 00:43:49,160
She is as strong-willed as her mother.

540
00:43:49,240 --> 00:43:52,680
But I've never seen Namthip
show this kind of determination.

541
00:43:56,160 --> 00:43:57,400
Puna wants to fight.

542
00:43:58,440 --> 00:44:02,080
If we try to stop her, we probably can't.

543
00:44:04,520 --> 00:44:05,480
Yeah, you're right.

544
00:44:06,000 --> 00:44:09,160
She's quietly stubborn.
The more we stop her, the more she rebels.

545
00:44:09,680 --> 00:44:13,400
So, what should we do now?

546
00:44:14,320 --> 00:44:15,520
We have to let her be

547
00:44:16,360 --> 00:44:17,960
and watch from a distance.

548
00:44:19,120 --> 00:44:22,880
When there's something we can do,
we'll step in.

549
00:44:24,480 --> 00:44:28,880
We won't let her take any more risks.
Can you do that?

550
00:44:32,800 --> 00:44:33,800
I can.

551
00:44:35,160 --> 00:44:36,120
From now on,

552
00:44:36,800 --> 00:44:40,760
anything risky, I'll handle it myself.

553
00:44:41,840 --> 00:44:43,760
Wilai, Tharin, you two should go back.

554
00:44:44,760 --> 00:44:46,080
It's not safe here.

555
00:44:48,000 --> 00:44:50,240
I'll take Puna home myself.

556
00:44:50,320 --> 00:44:53,640
-Please take care of her.
-Don't worry, we're family.

557
00:44:53,720 --> 00:44:55,160
Thank you so much, Teacher.

558
00:44:57,080 --> 00:44:57,960
Let's go.

559
00:45:10,080 --> 00:45:11,480
Thank you for giving me a ride.

560
00:45:12,080 --> 00:45:16,400
I believe Puna will recover
and be strong again soon.

561
00:45:18,520 --> 00:45:20,040
I hope so too.

562
00:45:21,840 --> 00:45:23,920
<i>The baby is really easy to take care of.</i>

563
00:45:24,000 --> 00:45:26,200
She doesn't cry at all during the night.

564
00:45:27,520 --> 00:45:30,080
Right now, she's playing with Phupha.

565
00:45:30,160 --> 00:45:32,120
Really? Well…

566
00:45:32,640 --> 00:45:35,880
-Does Phupha love Puna?
-Of course, he does.

567
00:45:36,680 --> 00:45:39,240
He's very attached to her now.

568
00:45:39,320 --> 00:45:42,120
I'm glad to hear that.

569
00:45:43,160 --> 00:45:44,160
On.

570
00:45:44,720 --> 00:45:47,200
I have something important to tell you.

571
00:45:48,000 --> 00:45:49,040
What is it?

572
00:45:49,120 --> 00:45:52,040
Is it okay

573
00:45:52,120 --> 00:45:54,320
if I marry Phupha?

574
00:46:02,280 --> 00:46:06,480
On, I'm sorry, I mean…

575
00:46:07,560 --> 00:46:11,440
Don't worry. I haven't said
anything bad to you.

576
00:46:13,840 --> 00:46:17,360
If you and Phupha truly love each other,

577
00:46:17,440 --> 00:46:19,040
I'm happy for you.

578
00:46:19,120 --> 00:46:21,720
<i>You're the friend I love most, you know?</i>

579
00:46:21,800 --> 00:46:24,360
I believe you'll take good care of him.

580
00:46:26,240 --> 00:46:29,320
I hope you two
will love each other very much.

581
00:46:34,240 --> 00:46:35,240
Tharin.

582
00:46:36,240 --> 00:46:38,480
Be careful on your way back.

583
00:46:39,600 --> 00:46:41,480
Watch out, in case
you run into Chart again.

584
00:46:44,320 --> 00:46:45,480
I'll be careful.

585
00:46:56,560 --> 00:46:59,080
Onanong, this is Kamnan Pong.

586
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:03,080
He's the owner of Darathong Music
that I told you about.

587
00:47:05,000 --> 00:47:06,080
Hello.

588
00:47:07,720 --> 00:47:09,160
Well, Kamnan Pong

589
00:47:09,240 --> 00:47:12,320
wants you to join his label as a singer.
What do you think?

590
00:47:12,400 --> 00:47:15,360
Oh, but aren't you making music anymore?

591
00:47:15,440 --> 00:47:18,120
Of course, I'm still
making music as usual.

592
00:47:18,200 --> 00:47:21,640
But my label is small.
We don't have a lot of funds.

593
00:47:21,720 --> 00:47:25,440
I'm looking for a bold partner
like Darathong Music to help out.

594
00:47:26,600 --> 00:47:29,280
For the next album, I'll have Kamnan Pong

595
00:47:29,360 --> 00:47:31,720
take care of the songs
and promotion for you as well.

596
00:47:34,000 --> 00:47:34,920
Alright, Boss.

597
00:47:35,000 --> 00:47:38,280
I hope we can work together well, Ms. On.

598
00:47:38,360 --> 00:47:40,760
Right now, I'm looking
for songs for the album.

599
00:47:40,840 --> 00:47:44,880
If you have any good songs
to suggest, feel free to share.

600
00:47:44,960 --> 00:47:46,600
Sure, Kamnan.

601
00:47:52,760 --> 00:47:54,040
From now on,

602
00:47:54,760 --> 00:47:59,080
you're officially a singer
under my Darathong Music.

603
00:48:00,880 --> 00:48:03,720
Thank you for letting me be part of it.

604
00:48:07,040 --> 00:48:08,360
It's my pleasure.

605
00:48:19,240 --> 00:48:22,000
Amazing! You nailed it in one take.

606
00:48:22,080 --> 00:48:23,400
Great job, On!

607
00:48:24,000 --> 00:48:24,960
Thank you.

608
00:48:25,040 --> 00:48:29,360
If I can improve anything,
let me know. I'm happy to adjust

609
00:48:30,680 --> 00:48:31,800
-Kamnan Pong.
-Yes?

610
00:48:31,880 --> 00:48:34,960
Look at this news!
The newspaper's making a big deal of it.

611
00:48:36,920 --> 00:48:38,600
ONANONG WONGWICHIAN

612
00:48:38,680 --> 00:48:41,920
The new sweetheart of Kamnan Pong

613
00:48:42,000 --> 00:48:43,520
is the bright-voiced singer

614
00:48:44,080 --> 00:48:47,760
from Darathong Music, with the initials O,

615
00:48:48,480 --> 00:48:49,960
and they're keeping it a secret.

616
00:48:52,760 --> 00:48:54,120
-You can go.
-Okay.

617
00:48:56,160 --> 00:48:59,040
This kind of news isn't good at all.

618
00:48:59,120 --> 00:49:01,880
I'm sorry for making you look bad, On.

619
00:49:03,880 --> 00:49:06,520
It's okay, I'll fix the news.

620
00:49:08,000 --> 00:49:12,120
But honestly, I do wish it were true,

621
00:49:12,200 --> 00:49:13,880
like the news says.

622
00:49:18,680 --> 00:49:20,440
Do you mind

623
00:49:21,400 --> 00:49:24,400
if we start seeing each other quietly?

624
00:49:28,960 --> 00:49:30,320
It's alright.

625
00:49:30,960 --> 00:49:32,440
You don't need to answer right away.

626
00:49:34,040 --> 00:49:37,000
For now, you can deny the news.

627
00:49:37,680 --> 00:49:41,120
When you're ready, we can talk.

628
00:49:45,240 --> 00:49:46,320
Yes, Kamnan Pong.

629
00:49:59,200 --> 00:50:01,160
I know you're tired, Puna.

630
00:50:01,240 --> 00:50:02,760
NEXT EPISODE

631
00:50:02,840 --> 00:50:05,560
-I'm here to support you.
-Thank you.

632
00:50:11,840 --> 00:50:13,120
Captain!

633
00:50:15,320 --> 00:50:18,200
<i>You're really pitiful. Look at me.</i>

634
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:22,200
I'm already so far ahead,
but you're still just a clothes ironer.

635
00:52:21,760 --> 00:52:24,680
Subtitle translation by:
Chomchanach Yanaharn
